data.name: labelLoading.Text
data.value:
Open Jagex Launcher, fully load a client, and then stop the import. All characters of that Jagex Account should be loaded.
You can import characters from different Jagex accounts by signing out, and into the other account.
Importing is only required for new characters, or to make your life easier if a login token expires.
Accounts that don't use Jagex Launcher must be manually entered in the accounts.csv file. The benefit is only to load specific profiles or client sizing.
